bug.summary: New converter in tf 2.2 does not propely convert PReLU operation
bug.description:
System information
OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04): Ubuntu 18.04 TensorFlow installed from (source or binary): TF Google Colaboratory TensorFlow version (or github SHA if from source): TF 2.2
Command used to run the converter or code if youâ€™re using the Python API <denchmark-code>def bilinear_resize(x, rsize): return tf.compat.v1.image.resize_bilinear(x, [rsize,rsize], align_corners=True)
model=load_model('/content/slim-net-157-0.02.hdf5',compile=False)
converter = tf.lite.TFLiteConverter.from_keras_model(model) tflite_model = converter.convert() open("model.tflite", "wb").write(tflite_model) </denchmark-code>
The output from the converter invocation <denchmark-code>1511172 </denchmark-code>
Also, please include a link to the saved model or GraphDef <denchmark-code>https://github.com/anilsathyan7/Portrait-Segmentation/blob/master/models/slim_seg_512/slim-net-157-0.02.hdf5 </denchmark-code>
The result is same for any model in general with PReLU operation Failure details If the conversion is successful, but the generated model is wrong, state what is wrong:
It splits PReLU into Neg, ReLU and Mul layers I need to run it using tflite gpu delegate which supports PReLU operation
Any other info / logs It produces correct results using old converter i.e with option converter.experimental_new_converter=False
